view.name: NYPD Complaint Data Historic
view.description: This dataset includes all valid felony, misdemeanor, and violation crimes reported to the New York City Police Department (NYPD) from 2006 to the end of last year (2017). For additional details, please see the attached data dictionary in the ‘About’ section.

columns.name: JURISDICTION_CODE
columns.description: Jurisdiction responsible for incident. Either internal, like Police(0), Transit(1), and Housing(2); or external(3), like Correction, Port Authority, etc.

columns.name: TRANSIT_DISTRICT
columns.description: Transit district in which the offense occurred.

columns.name: PATROL_BORO
columns.description: The name of the patrol borough in which the incident occurred
